"{\"uid\": \"cbsnews.com-news-tipping-in-france-paris-olympics-cbs-news-explains\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Watch CBS News Updated on: May 25, 2024 / 1:04 PM EDT/ CBS News Americans areoften unclearon when to tip stateside, let alone what customs apply in France.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 158, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 57, \"end\": 65, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_News\", \"score\": 0.9999999280430555, \"rank\": 7.195533835123363e-08, \"text\": \"CBS News\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_News\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_News\"}, {\"begin\": 151, \"end\": 157, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9701081757876016, \"rank\": 0.030547151655373368, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"CBS News\", \"from\": 6, \"to\": 14}, {\"ngram\": \"1:04 PM EDT/\", \"from\": 42, \"to\": 54}, {\"ngram\": \"unclearon\", \"from\": 83, \"to\": 92}, {\"ngram\": \"customs\", \"from\": 131, \"to\": 138}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So as they prepare to join the 15 million people around the world traveling to Paris for the upcomingOlympics, some U.S. tourists could use a primer on tipping etiquette in theCity of Light.\", \"from\": 159, \"to\": 349, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 238, \"end\": 243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999427018, \"rank\": 5.736409521908174e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the 15 million people\", \"from\": 186, \"to\": 207}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 215, \"to\": 224}, {\"ngram\": \"the upcomingOlympics\", \"from\": 248, \"to\": 268}, {\"ngram\": \"some U.S. tourists\", \"from\": 270, \"to\": 288}, {\"ngram\": \"a primer\", \"from\": 299, \"to\": 307}, {\"ngram\": \"etiquette\", \"from\": 319, \"to\": 328}, {\"ngram\": \"theCity\", \"from\": 332, \"to\": 339}, {\"ngram\": \"Light\", \"from\": 343, \"to\": 348}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While changing tipping norms at home can leave American consumers frustrated overubiquitous gratuity prompts, a completely different set of unspoken rules govern tipping expectations overseas - and some French restaurant operators may be eager to take advantage of foreigners' ignorance.\", \"from\": 351, \"to\": 638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 398, \"end\": 406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999238603438536, \"rank\": 7.614543349199139e-05, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 554, \"end\": 560, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999999285851143, \"rank\": 6.732726258593555e-08, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"norms\", \"from\": 374, \"to\": 379}, {\"ngram\": \"home\", \"from\": 383, \"to\": 387}, {\"ngram\": \"overubiquitous gratuity prompts\", \"from\": 428, \"to\": 459}, {\"ngram\": \"a completely different set\", \"from\": 461, \"to\": 487}, {\"ngram\": \"unspoken rules\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 505}, {\"ngram\": \"tipping expectations\", \"from\": 513, \"to\": 533}, {\"ngram\": \"advantage\", \"from\": 603, \"to\": 612}, {\"ngram\": \"foreigners' ignorance\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 637}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At restaurants in France, bills automatically include a service fee of 15% to cover servers' wages, so waitstaff there are typically far less dependent on tips to earn a living wage, as they are in the U.S.\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 846, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 658, \"end\": 664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9701081757876016, \"rank\": 0.030547151655373368, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"restaurants\", \"from\": 643, \"to\": 654}, {\"ngram\": \"bills\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 671}, {\"ngram\": \"a service fee\", \"from\": 694, \"to\": 707}, {\"ngram\": \"15%\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 714}, {\"ngram\": \"servers' wages\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 738}, {\"ngram\": \"tips\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 799}, {\"ngram\": \"a living wage\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 821}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 838, \"to\": 846}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, it's up to the discretion of the patron to decide if the service was good enough to warrant an extra gratuity of a couple Euros, referred to as a \\\"pourboire\\\" (literally meaning \\\"for drink\\\").\", \"from\": 847, \"to\": 1046, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the discretion\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 881}, {\"ngram\": \"the patron\", \"from\": 885, \"to\": 895}, {\"ngram\": \"the service\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 920}, {\"ngram\": \"an extra gratuity\", \"from\": 948, \"to\": 965}, {\"ngram\": \"a couple Euros\", \"from\": 969, \"to\": 983}, {\"ngram\": \"a \\\"pourboire\", \"from\": 1000, \"to\": 1012}, {\"ngram\": \"drink\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1043}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Another cultural difference: All manner of service people, including waiters and salespeople, are often less solicitous of customers than they are in the U.S., in part because good service does not invite the same kind of monetary reward as in the U.S.\", \"from\": 1048, \"to\": 1300, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Another cultural difference\", \"from\": 1048, \"to\": 1075}, {\"ngram\": \"All manner\", \"from\": 1077, \"to\": 1087}, {\"ngram\": \"service people\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1105}, {\"ngram\": \"waiters\", \"from\": 1117, \"to\": 1124}, {\"ngram\": \"salespeople\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1140}, {\"ngram\": \"customers\", \"from\": 1171, \"to\": 1180}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 1198, \"to\": 1206}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1211, \"to\": 1215}, {\"ngram\": \"good service\", \"from\": 1224, \"to\": 1236}, {\"ngram\": \"the same kind\", \"from\": 1253, \"to\": 1266}, {\"ngram\": \"monetary reward\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1285}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 1292, \"to\": 1300}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In other words, do not expect your waiter to introduce herself by name, American-style - or to serve your food with an ingratiating smile.\", \"from\": 1301, \"to\": 1439, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other words\", \"from\": 1304, \"to\": 1315}, {\"ngram\": \"your waiter\", \"from\": 1331, \"to\": 1342}, {\"ngram\": \"name\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1371}, {\"ngram\": \"American-style\", \"from\": 1373, \"to\": 1387}, {\"ngram\": \"your food\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1411}, {\"ngram\": \"an ingratiating smile\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1438}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The expression of service is not necessarily fast and attentive like it is here in U.S.,\\\" said Erika Rodriguez, an operations specialist at travel site Going.com, who has spent the past four summers in France.\", \"from\": 1441, \"to\": 1651, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1537, \"end\": 1542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erika_Mann\", \"score\": 0.9999988690457968, \"rank\": 1.1199527735757672e-06, \"text\": \"Erika\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erika_Mann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Erika_Mann\"}, {\"begin\": 1644, \"end\": 1650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9701081757876016, \"rank\": 0.030547151655373368, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The expression\", \"from\": 1442, \"to\": 1456}, {\"ngram\": \"service\", \"from\": 1460, \"to\": 1467}, {\"ngram\": \"U.S.\", \"from\": 1525, \"to\": 1529}, {\"ngram\": \"an operations specialist\", \"from\": 1554, \"to\": 1578}, {\"ngram\": \"travel site Going.com\", \"from\": 1582, \"to\": 1603}, {\"ngram\": \"the past four summers\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1640}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's not to say it's a bad experience, but they want to make clear they are not your servant.\", \"from\": 1652, \"to\": 1748, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a bad experience\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1692}, {\"ngram\": \"your servant\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1747}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are very direct.\\\"\", \"from\": 1749, \"to\": 1771, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's no secret that European establishments often prefer Americans over other nationalities of tourists precisely because they are inclined to tip.\", \"from\": 1773, \"to\": 1920, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no secret\", \"from\": 1778, \"to\": 1787}, {\"ngram\": \"European establishments\", \"from\": 1793, \"to\": 1816}, {\"ngram\": \"Americans\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1839}, {\"ngram\": \"other nationalities\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 1864}, {\"ngram\": \"tourists\", \"from\": 1868, \"to\": 1876}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And some visitors to France report that restaurants are trying to squeeze extra cash out of tourists by encouraging them to leave the kind of gratuity they would in the U.S.\", \"from\": 1921, \"to\": 2094, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1942, \"end\": 1948, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9701081757876016, \"rank\": 0.030547151655373368, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some visitors\", \"from\": 1925, \"to\": 1938}, {\"ngram\": \"restaurants\", \"from\": 1961, \"to\": 1972}, {\"ngram\": \"extra cash\", \"from\": 1995, \"to\": 2005}, {\"ngram\": \"tourists\", \"from\": 2013, \"to\": 2021}, {\"ngram\": \"the kind\", \"from\": 2051, \"to\": 2059}, {\"ngram\": \"gratuity\", \"from\": 2063, \"to\": 2071}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 2086, \"to\": 2094}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The trick was so common in St. Bart's the last time she visited, that travel guru Melissa Biggs Bradley, founder of the Indagare travel agency, referred to it as \\\"the St. Bart's scam.\\\"\", \"from\": 2096, \"to\": 2280, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2127, \"end\": 2131, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bart_Simpson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.4897121366222115e-24, \"text\": \"Bart\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bart_Simpson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bart_Simpson\"}, {\"begin\": 2178, \"end\": 2185, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melissa\", \"score\": 0.792921412588026, \"rank\": 0.2598816888509194, \"text\": \"Melissa\", \"types\": [\"Q82799\", \"Q202444\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melissa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melissa\"}, {\"begin\": 2192, \"end\": 2199, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omar_Bradley\", \"score\": 0.9759673511114817, \"rank\": 0.02451871624821197, \"text\": \"Bradley\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omar_Bradley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omar_Bradley\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The trick\", \"from\": 2096, \"to\": 2105}, {\"ngram\": \"founder\", \"from\": 2201, \"to\": 2208}, {\"ngram\": \"the Indagare travel agency\", \"from\": 2212, \"to\": 2238}, {\"ngram\": \"the St. Bart's scam\", \"from\": 2259, \"to\": 2278}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"All the restaurants were asking people if they would like to leave tips without acknowledging that gratuity is built in,\\\" Bradley told CBS MoneyWatch.\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2433, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2405, \"end\": 2412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omar_Bradley\", \"score\": 0.9759673511114817, \"rank\": 0.02451871624821197, \"text\": \"Bradley\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omar_Bradley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omar_Bradley\"}, {\"begin\": 2418, \"end\": 2432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_MoneyWatch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"CBS MoneyWatch\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_MoneyWatch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_MoneyWatch\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"All the restaurants\", \"from\": 2283, \"to\": 2302}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2315, \"to\": 2321}, {\"ngram\": \"tips\", \"from\": 2350, \"to\": 2354}, {\"ngram\": \"gratuity\", \"from\": 2382, \"to\": 2390}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Going.com's Rodriguez noted that in Paris, that tactic is more common in touristy spots than at restaurants that mostly draw locals.\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2471, \"end\": 2476, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999427018, \"rank\": 5.736409521908174e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Going.com's Rodriguez\", \"from\": 2435, \"to\": 2456}, {\"ngram\": \"tactic\", \"from\": 2483, \"to\": 2489}, {\"ngram\": \"touristy spots\", \"from\": 2508, \"to\": 2522}, {\"ngram\": \"restaurants\", \"from\": 2531, \"to\": 2542}, {\"ngram\": \"locals\", \"from\": 2560, \"to\": 2566}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"They bring you a credit card machine with suggested tips comparable to amounts you leave in the U.S.,\\\" she told CBS MoneyWatch.\", \"from\": 2568, \"to\": 2696, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2681, \"end\": 2695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_MoneyWatch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"CBS MoneyWatch\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_MoneyWatch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_MoneyWatch\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a credit card machine\", \"from\": 2584, \"to\": 2605}, {\"ngram\": \"suggested tips\", \"from\": 2611, \"to\": 2625}, {\"ngram\": \"amounts\", \"from\": 2640, \"to\": 2647}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 2661, \"to\": 2669}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While that is hardly illegal, experts say it does amount to taking advantage of diners who are unfamiliar with foreign customs.\", \"from\": 2698, \"to\": 2825, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"experts\", \"from\": 2728, \"to\": 2735}, {\"ngram\": \"advantage\", \"from\": 2765, \"to\": 2774}, {\"ngram\": \"diners\", \"from\": 2778, \"to\": 2784}, {\"ngram\": \"foreign customs\", \"from\": 2809, \"to\": 2824}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brian Warrener, who has researched tipping norms across Europe and how they differ from those in the U.S., said that at some restaurants in France he detected what he called \\\"a little bit of a bending of the rules.\\\"\", \"from\": 2827, \"to\": 3042, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2967, \"end\": 2973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9701081757876016, \"rank\": 0.030547151655373368, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Brian Warrener\", \"from\": 2827, \"to\": 2841}, {\"ngram\": \"norms\", \"from\": 2870, \"to\": 2875}, {\"ngram\": \"Europe\", \"from\": 2883, \"to\": 2889}, {\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 2924, \"to\": 2932}, {\"ngram\": \"some restaurants\", \"from\": 2947, \"to\": 2963}, {\"ngram\": \"a little bit\", \"from\": 3002, \"to\": 3014}, {\"ngram\": \"a bending\", \"from\": 3018, \"to\": 3027}, {\"ngram\": \"the rules\", \"from\": 3031, \"to\": 3040}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Especially in places where lots of Americans are traveling, restaurants will include a line on the bottom in English saying tipping is not included, even though there is a 15% service charge,\\\" Warrener told CBS MoneyWatch.\", \"from\": 3044, \"to\": 3267, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3252, \"end\": 3266, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_MoneyWatch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"CBS MoneyWatch\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_MoneyWatch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/CBS_MoneyWatch\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"places\", \"from\": 3059, \"to\": 3065}, {\"ngram\": \"lots\", \"from\": 3072, \"to\": 3076}, {\"ngram\": \"Americans\", \"from\": 3080, \"to\": 3089}, {\"ngram\": \"restaurants\", \"from\": 3105, \"to\": 3116}, {\"ngram\": \"a line\", \"from\": 3130, \"to\": 3136}, {\"ngram\": \"the bottom\", \"from\": 3140, \"to\": 3150}, {\"ngram\": \"English\", \"from\": 3154, \"to\": 3161}, {\"ngram\": \"tipping\", \"from\": 3169, \"to\": 3176}, {\"ngram\": \"a 15% service charge\", \"from\": 3215, \"to\": 3235}, {\"ngram\": \"Warrener\", \"from\": 3238, \"to\": 3246}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"So they are clearly trying to communicate to folks who may not know the tipping norms in France.\\\"\", \"from\": 3268, \"to\": 3366, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3358, \"end\": 3364, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9701081757876016, \"rank\": 0.030547151655373368, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"folks\", \"from\": 3314, \"to\": 3319}, {\"ngram\": \"the tipping norms\", \"from\": 3337, \"to\": 3354}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He noted that some operators use tablets to accept payment that include prompts for tips of 15% to 30%, a practice he suspects is becoming more widespread in anticipation of visitors arriving in Paris for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 3368, \"to\": 3586, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3563, \"end\": 3568, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999427018, \"rank\": 5.736409521908174e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some operators\", \"from\": 3382, \"to\": 3396}, {\"ngram\": \"tablets\", \"from\": 3401, \"to\": 3408}, {\"ngram\": \"payment\", \"from\": 3419, \"to\": 3426}, {\"ngram\": \"prompts\", \"from\": 3440, \"to\": 3447}, {\"ngram\": \"tips\", \"from\": 3452, \"to\": 3456}, {\"ngram\": \"15% to 30%\", \"from\": 3460, \"to\": 3470}, {\"ngram\": \"a practice\", \"from\": 3472, \"to\": 3482}, {\"ngram\": \"anticipation\", \"from\": 3526, \"to\": 3538}, {\"ngram\": \"visitors\", \"from\": 3542, \"to\": 3550}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 3573, \"to\": 3585}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In the U.S., that would be an inflated tip, but in France, where tipping is not part of compensation, it's taking advantage,\\\" Warrener said.\", \"from\": 3588, \"to\": 3729, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3640, \"end\": 3646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9701081757876016, \"rank\": 0.030547151655373368, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the U.S.\", \"from\": 3592, \"to\": 3600}, {\"ngram\": \"an inflated tip\", \"from\": 3616, \"to\": 3631}, {\"ngram\": \"tipping\", \"from\": 3654, \"to\": 3661}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 3669, \"to\": 3673}, {\"ngram\": \"compensation\", \"from\": 3677, \"to\": 3689}, {\"ngram\": \"advantage\", \"from\": 3703, \"to\": 3712}, {\"ngram\": \"Warrener\", \"from\": 3715, \"to\": 3723}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bradley of Indagare offered advice for avoiding such tipping ruses.\", \"from\": 3731, \"to\": 3798, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Bradley\", \"from\": 3731, \"to\": 3738}, {\"ngram\": \"Indagare\", \"from\": 3742, \"to\": 3750}, {\"ngram\": \"advice\", \"from\": 3759, \"to\": 3765}, {\"ngram\": \"such tipping ruses\", \"from\": 3779, \"to\": 3797}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"If you pay by credit card and are prompted to leave a tip, ask if service is included,\\\" Bradley said.\", \"from\": 3799, \"to\": 3901, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3888, \"end\": 3895, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omar_Bradley\", \"score\": 0.9759673511114817, \"rank\": 0.02451871624821197, \"text\": \"Bradley\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omar_Bradley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Omar_Bradley\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"credit card\", \"from\": 3814, \"to\": 3825}, {\"ngram\": \"a tip\", \"from\": 3852, \"to\": 3857}, {\"ngram\": \"service\", \"from\": 3866, \"to\": 3873}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Be forewarned: \\\"They might try to fudge it, but they can not say 'no' when it is.\", \"from\": 3903, \"to\": 3984, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They could say it's a question of whether or not you want to give me something for nice service.\", \"from\": 3985, \"to\": 4081, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a question\", \"from\": 4005, \"to\": 4015}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 4054, \"to\": 4063}, {\"ngram\": \"nice service\", \"from\": 4068, \"to\": 4080}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it's absolutely standard, so the assumption should be you are paying the service,\\\" she added.\", \"from\": 4082, \"to\": 4179, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the assumption\", \"from\": 4115, \"to\": 4129}, {\"ngram\": \"the service\", \"from\": 4155, \"to\": 4166}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Given that a service charge is already baked into the total cost of a meal, servers are not expecting a whole lot extra.\", \"from\": 4181, \"to\": 4301, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a service charge\", \"from\": 4192, \"to\": 4208}, {\"ngram\": \"the total cost\", \"from\": 4231, \"to\": 4245}, {\"ngram\": \"a meal\", \"from\": 4249, \"to\": 4255}, {\"ngram\": \"servers\", \"from\": 4257, \"to\": 4264}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But it is common to leave some loose change if you are getting a coffee or meal in reward for good service.\", \"from\": 4302, \"to\": 4409, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some loose change\", \"from\": 4328, \"to\": 4345}, {\"ngram\": \"a coffee\", \"from\": 4365, \"to\": 4373}, {\"ngram\": \"meal\", \"from\": 4377, \"to\": 4381}, {\"ngram\": \"reward\", \"from\": 4385, \"to\": 4391}, {\"ngram\": \"good service\", \"from\": 4396, \"to\": 4408}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For example, rounding up a bill from 13.50 Euros to 14 Euros, or leaving a few Euros, is usually sufficient.\", \"from\": 4410, \"to\": 4518, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"example\", \"from\": 4414, \"to\": 4421}, {\"ngram\": \"a bill\", \"from\": 4435, \"to\": 4441}, {\"ngram\": \"13.50 Euros\", \"from\": 4447, \"to\": 4458}, {\"ngram\": \"14 Euros\", \"from\": 4462, \"to\": 4470}, {\"ngram\": \"a few Euros\", \"from\": 4483, \"to\": 4494}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"What Europeans are accustomed to doing when they get good service is they will round up the bill to say, 'Nice job, here's a little something extra,'\\\" Warrener said.\", \"from\": 4520, \"to\": 4686, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"What Europeans\", \"from\": 4521, \"to\": 4535}, {\"ngram\": \"good service\", \"from\": 4574, \"to\": 4586}, {\"ngram\": \"the bill\", \"from\": 4609, \"to\": 4617}, {\"ngram\": 